September 2023
Please read this Privacy Notice carefully.  It describes how Willis Towers Watson, which operates worldwide through its subsidiaries and affiliates (collectively, “Willis Towers Watson”, “we” or “our”), collects and processes your Personal Information which it obtains through the provision and operation of our Applications and Services (as defined below), including the use of our administration and brokerage technology solutions which may be accessed by you through Embark.
When we use the term “
Application
” or “
Applications
” in this Privacy Notice, we are referring collectively to the administration and brokerage technology solution applications themselves, and/or the Embark application.  When we refer to an Application or Applications together with related products or services which we provide to clients for your use, we use the term “
Services
.”  Both our Applications and Services may be accessed either through a mobile device using a dedicated Application or through any device with a browser via this website and other websites which we control and link to this Privacy Notice.
For purposes of the General Data Protection Regulation (“
GDPR
”) and similar laws, you will find a list of our Services, related Applications and identified controllers in the section
Listing of Services
,
Applications and Classifications
.  Residents of the European Union/European Economic Area (“
EU/EEA
”), Switzerland, the United Kingdom (“
UK
”), Turkey, Brazil, the Philippines or Mainland China, please see the section
Additional Information for Residents of Certain Jurisdictions
for more information specific to you.
In this Privacy Notice where we refer to
Personal Information
, we mean information that identifies you, and/or as appropriate, your dependents and/or beneficiaries, either directly or indirectly.
Our use of the term “Personal Information” in this Privacy Notice includes other similar terms under applicable privacy laws - such as “personal data” and “personally identifiable information.”   In general, Personal Information includes any information that identifies, relates to, describes, or is reasonably capable of being associated, linked, or linkable with a particular individual.  We also refer to our “
Clients
” which means your current, prospective, or former employer or other employers that use the Services, including the Plan Trustee or Plan Sponsor, where appropriate, or any other services we offer through the Applications.
In this Privacy Notice we describe the collection, use, disclosure, and processing of Personal Information that we collect through the Applications and when we provide the Services. Separately, there are
Terms of Use
which explain how the Applications are to be used.
Our collection, use, and disclosure and processing of Personal Information about individuals will vary depending upon the circumstances and Services we provide.  This Privacy Notice is intended to describe the overall privacy and data protection practices associated with the Services and Applications.  In some cases, different or additional notices about our data collection and processing practices may be provided and apply to our processing of certain personal information or use of certain applications or services.  For more information, please see the sections
Listing of Services, Applications and Classifications
and
Additional Information for Residents of Certain Jurisdictions
for additional information specific to you.
This Privacy Notice also applies to Personal Information provided by our Clients (who may be your current, prospective, or former employer, Plan Trustee or Plan Sponsor), that we collect through your use of the Services and Applications, or at times, may be collected from other sources including from our Clients directly. This can be Personal Information you provide about yourself, and/or as appropriate, about your dependents and/or beneficiaries. By providing the Personal Information of dependents or beneficiaries, you represent that you have the proper authority or their consent to provide their Personal Information to us.
In providing the Services enabled by the Applications or other technology solutions used by you as a prospective, current or former employee of our Clients, we are required to comply with applicable data protection laws including the EU GDPR, member states’ supplementary laws, the UK GDPR, the Swiss Federal Act on Data Protection, Brazil’s Lei Geral de Proteção de Dados (“
LGPD
”), China Personal Information Protection Law (
"PIPL"
) and other similar laws.   These data protection laws impose obligations on us relating to our collection and use of your Personal Information. You will find a list of our Services offered in the EU and other regions, along with our data role classification under the GDPR or other similar laws for those Services (which will vary depending on exact circumstances) in the section
Listing of Services, Applications and Classifications
.
Under the GDPR, where we act in our capacity as a “controller” with respect to Personal Information, this Privacy Notice will apply, as explained below.  Furthermore, Willis Towers Watson plc is the controller, unless the processing is controlled by another Willis Towers Watson entity.  With respect to our Services and other business activities, in general, the Willis Towers Watson group company with whom you engage is the controller for your Personal Information, together with Willis Towers Watson plc, the parent company for the Willis Towers Watson group.  You can find information about exceptions to this controller entity along with a list of our Services which operate under the GDPR and similar laws, and associated GDPR and similar classifications in the section
