The type and amount of Personal Information which we collect, sometimes partly or entirely automatically or non-automatically, will vary depending on various factors, including your personal circumstances, but may include any combination of the following if necessary and applicable related to you, your dependents, or your beneficiaries:
contact details such as name, postal address, email address, and telephone number and other similar contact information;
gender, age, date of birth, marital status, nationality, country of residence, occupation, employment details, hobbies, family composition, dependents, and other similar demographic information;
your unique personal identifiers such as Social Security number, Social Insurance number, bank account numbers and transaction details, passport number, and employee number;
human resources data, such as job title and role; benefits and compensation information; dependent/beneficiary information; educational, academic and professional qualifications information; emergency contact information; and performance management information;
information about your finances, property and assets, such as details of your income and existing pension/insurance arrangements and amounts insured/claimed;
physical or mental conditions, medical reports, hospitals and heath institutions, health insurance information (including salary), premiums in the past, the date of beginning of insurance coverage, personal health exceptions, additional premiums, general exceptions, amendments, premiums, damages paid under health insurance, personal retirement plan schemes and salaries, contributions, total accumulations, and fund allocation;
information about physical or mental health, including medical reports, hospital and health institutions utilized, medical history, description of illness or injury suffered, and any specific treatment received if required for insurance underwriting purposes. In some jurisdictions this is considered Sensitive Personal Information;
information about you which we are obliged to check for legal or regulatory reasons, such as information relating to your identity and if relevant, your criminal history (including allegations of crimes). In some jurisdictions this is considered Sensitive Personal Information;
details of the events which WTW collects and processes in connection with the provision of services (including the Services), for example, details of events which cause any insurance indemnity sent by you or on your behalf through our Applications and Services, and information about your access and use of our Applications and Services, as set out in this Privacy Notice and applicable Cookie Notices.  We also monitor device event information;
statements made by or about you, and records of communications;
other information which we collect and process in connection with the provision of the Services, such as policy information, claims information, benefits selections and payment records;
information you may voluntarily submit to us by completing any form on our websites;
we may also collect Personal Information through offline channels, such as when you call our service centers.
We may collect Personal Information from the following sources:
from you,
from our Client, your prospective, current or former employer, who may also be a controller with respect to your Personal Information and you may wish to consult with them in the first instance if you have any questions about the processing of Personal Information,
from the Plan Trustee or Plan Sponsor, such as through data files received from the Plan Trustee or Plan Sponsor,
through our Services, such as when you model your benefits or provide or make changes through our websites,
offline, such as through mail or when you contact our telephone service centers, if any,
from other sources, including public records, third parties engaged by the Plan Trustee or Plan Sponsor to provide benefits-related services, public sources, insurance companies, government agencies along with regulatory and tax authorities or other organizations with whom you have dealings.
We will collect Personal Information only for one or more of the purposes described in the section
Legal Bases for Processing Personal Information
.
It is not mandatory for you to provide any Personal Information, but a failure to do so might impact or restrict the type of service we are able to provide to you or your prospective, current or former employer.
Where required by local laws to obtain express consent to any processing activity envisaged by this notice, we will do so before processing your Personal Information.   Where we must have a legal basis to process Personal Information, in most cases the legal basis will be one of the following:
for our legitimate interests, for example to provide services to our clients (including the Services), to ensure that the Services are appropriate, available and secure, to improve our Services, manage our risks, maintain accurate transaction records, and manage our business in an efficient way,
for the legitimate interests of our clients and other third parties (for example, to investigate and assess claims made against policies held or underwritten by them and to prevent and detect suspicions of fraud),
to comply with our legal obligations such as due diligence and reporting obligations,
to perform a contract with you,
explicitly as required by laws,
where required to enable us as a data controller to fulfil our legal responsibilities, or
for the legitimate interests or benefits of our Clients, where they are data controllers, provided that your fundamental rights and liberties are not damaged.
Some of the categories of information that we collect are special categories of Personal Information ("Sensitive Personal Information"). These include your health records (such as your medical history and reports on medical diagnoses, injuries and treatment); information about your personal characteristics and circumstances of a sensitive nature such as your racial or ethnic origin, sex life, mental and physical health and genetic information.  We process Sensitive Personal Information on the following legal bases:
consent which you have provided to your prospective, current or former employer. You may withdraw your consent at any time by contacting us as set forth in the
Contacts & Comments
section. Where we use Personal Information of your dependents and/or beneficiaries, they also have this right,
to establish, exercise or defend legal claims,
where legislation otherwise permits us to process Sensitive Personal Information (for example, where the processing is necessary for insurance purposes).
We use Personal Information as follows:
so that you can access and sign into the Applications, to deal with your questions and process any Personal Information you provide when you contact us with questions or provide information through the Applications’ support feature,
to display your benefit or other summary information and provide access to the Applications which provide the details of this information,
to provide the Services and fulfil our contractual obligations to our clients,
to conduct data analysis, including on use of the Applications and Services,
for fraud monitoring, investigation, prevention, detection and where necessary to take action,
to help develop new services and to enhance, improve or modify our services,
to operate and expand our business activities,
to carry out background checks and conduct due diligence if legally required to do so,
to perform administrative activities in connection with our Services,
to exercise, defend or protect our legal rights or the rights of our clients or third parties, and
to comply with legal and professional obligations and to cooperate with regulatory bodies.
Our uses of Personal Information will always be subject to and consistent with our contractual agreements with our Clients, including Plan Trustees and PlanSponsors.
We also analyze Personal Information for the purposes of risk assessment, fraud prevention and detection, and to report to our clients as part of the Services.  The way we analyze Personal Information for the purposes of risk assessment, fraud prevention and detection, and to report to our clients as part of the Services may involve profiling, which means that we may process your Personal Information using software that is able to evaluate your personal aspects and predict risks or outcomes.
We may also aggregate, de-identify or anonymize Personal Information. Aggregated, de-identified or anonymized data is not capable of identifying individuals and is not treated as Personal Information under this Privacy Notice.
Except as set forth herein, we do not sell or share Personal Information with third parties for their own separate use. Rather, data may be shared with third parties retained by Willis Towers Watson for purposes of fulfilling their obligations to Willis Towers Watson only.
Because we are a global company, and subject to our contractual commitments to individual Clients, except as set forth below, Personal Information may be transferred to, stored, and processed by one of our affiliates or subsidiaries in a country that is not regarded as ensuring an adequate level of protection for Personal Information under applicable law (including Bermuda, the European Union, India, Quebec, the United States, and other jurisdictions, in which we or our service providers operate (including European Union law). We have put in place appropriate safeguards (such as contractual commitments) in accordance with applicable legal requirements to ensure that your data is adequately protected. For more information on the appropriate safeguards in place, please contact us as set forth in the
Contacts & Comments
section.  For Benefits Access and Pension Access, our data is maintained in the Netherlands and Ireland.  For Employee Engagement Surveys our data is maintained in Reigate, UK.
For the delivery of our Services and Applications, we may use external service providers such as Microsoft Azure and Amazon AWS.   We request our external service providers to implement and apply security safeguards to ensure the privacy and security of your Personal Information. These third parties have agreed to confidentiality restrictions and to use of any Personal Information we share with them or which they collect on our behalf solely for the purpose of providing the contracted service to us.
We may share Personal Information with third parties under the following circumstances:
to any Willis Towers Watson group company for the uses and purposes set out above,
to our clients, intermediaries, advisers and business partners (such as insurance companies) for the purposes of fulfilling our contractual obligations to clients, for example to deliver our services (including the Services) and to arrange insurance products for you and our clients,
to third party service providers such as entities providing customer service, email delivery, auditing and other services,
to any court, regulator, law enforcement agency, government body or professional body, if we are obliged to disclose Personal Information under applicable law or regulation, which may include laws outside your country of residence,
in the event of any reorganization, merger, sale, joint venture, assignment, transfer or other disposition of all or any portion of our business, assets or stock (including in connection with any bankruptcy or similar proceedings) your Personal Information may be shared with the acquiring or successor entity along with its affiliates and subsidiaries.
In certain cases, we may share Personal Information with additional service providers offered by your employer through your employment relationship. We do this on the instructions of your employer. For more information on the appropriate safeguards in place in relation to this transfer, please check your employer’s privacy notice.
You may request to review, make amendments, have deleted or otherwise exercise your rights under applicable privacy laws over your personal information that we hold, subject to certain limitations under applicable law.
