The Services may include links to websites for your employer, Plan Trustee or Plan Sponsor and other third parties such as insurance carriers, government agencies, and financial service providers. If you access these links, you will be leaving the Services. Your use of such third-party sites is governed by the privacy policies of those third parties, not by this Privacy Notice. This Privacy Notice does not address, and we are not responsible for, the privacy, information, or other practices of any third parties, including the Plan Trustee, Plan Sponsor or any third party operating any site or service to which the Services may link. The inclusion of a link on the Services does not imply endorsement of the linked site or service by us or by our affiliates.
Willis Towers Watson maintains appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect the security of your data against loss, misuse, unauthorized access, disclosure or alteration. These measures are aimed at ensuring the ongoing integrity and confidentiality of Personal Information. We evaluate these measures on a regular basis to ensure the security of the processing.
We will retain Personal Information for as long as is necessary for the provision of Services.  When we no longer need Personal Information in connection with the Services, we will then retain Personal Information for a period of time that reasonably allows us to:
comply with our regulatory obligations;
maintain business records for analysis and/or audit purposes;
commence or defend legal claims;
comply with records retention requirements under applicable laws or regulations;
comply with legal or other regulatory obligations; defend or bring any existing or potential legal claims; and
deal with any complaints regarding our activities.
We will delete your Personal Information when it is no longer required for these purposes. If there is any information that we are unable, for technical reasons, to delete entirely from our systems, we will put in place appropriate measures to prevent any further processing or use of the data.  We may retain aggregated or anonymized data (which is not treated as Personal Information under this Privacy Notice) for longer.
If you have reason to believe that your interaction with us is no longer secure (for example, if you believe that the security of your account has been compromised), please immediately notify us in accordance with the
Contacts & Comments
section.
We have the capability to monitor your access and use of the Services and Applications.  We may make use of such monitoring capability where this is considered necessary to protect Personal Information.  Such monitoring forms part of the information security measures deployed by us.
The Applications and Services are not directed to individuals under certain ages as prescribed by local laws (“Minors”).  We do not knowingly collect Personal Information from Minors.  By providing the Personal Information of dependents or beneficiaries who may be Minors, you represent that you have the proper authority or consent from those with proper authority to provide their Personal Information to us.
